## Conventions

- Every error caught is logged here at session close (TEST or DOCUMENT phase), even if fixed within the session.
- Critical-severity errors trigger an immediate HITL escalation at next checkpoint.
- A pattern is "novel" when no AIE-NNN entry in `errors_catalog.json` matches the cause. Novel patterns are added to the catalog with `preloaded: false` and `first_seen_session: <id>`.
- The catalog is auto-extending; this narrative file is **the human story**. Both must be in sync.
